result.name: Veggie Palace

reviews.text:
Chinese style vegetarian restaurant, very lovely food. On the 1st floor of an old commercial building, a bit hidden.
The restaurant serves set menu so no A la carte option available, however, all the dishes we ate were delicious so no need to worry!
Have to book in advance (especially during weekend) as the restaurant is quite popular.
A very good choice for vegetarians!

Buddhist restaurant that serves a set vegetarian menu. There's one price (cheap, about $260), and then you get served with a series of vegetarian dishes (at least 9, maybe more).
Yes it is vegetables, but the dishes are excellent. Their use of tofu and mushrooms give their food a lovely texture and flavour. It will be an experience for any meat eater to try and you will see just what can be done with tofu.

This restaurant come highly recommended for anyone but definitely for vegetarians, however I don't think this is vegan.
You do need to book well ahead as it can be hard to get a place here.
Nice food. Chinese style decorations. Seems enjoying French food
They offer special options for veggies food, go to come with a group
